# Release Notes Standards

When writing or updating CHANGELOG.md or any release notes:

- **Never use "Unreleased" sections** in a versioned release. Every entry must be under a concrete version heading (e.g., `## [1.2.0] - 2026-02-22`).
- **Never use placeholder text** like "TBD", "Coming soon", "To be determined", or "TODO" in release entries.
- **Never include empty sections** (e.g., `### Added` with no bullet points beneath it).
- When bumping a version, move any accumulated unreleased notes into the new version heading immediately â€” do not leave an `[Unreleased]` section alongside the new version.
- Every version entry must have a date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format.
